lish language level and academic goals.    Tutorium IEP > UIC Degree Program   Study full-time in our Intensive English Program.  Apply to a university degree program while finishing our highest level.   The Tutorium can help with the application process for UIC undergraduate and graduate degrees .   Tutorium IEP > UIC Global pathway program > UIC Degree Program   Study full-time in our Intensive English Program  Then, apply to the UIC Global pathway program. Not sure which program is best for you? Contact us .    UIC  Global pathway program (English   UIC Degree Courses) > UIC Degree Program   Attend the UIC Global pathway program. Not sure which program is best for you? Contact us .  Then, take evening, weekend or online English language courses provided by the Tutorium while completing degree courses in your field.    UIC Degree Program   Language Support Courses   While studying as an undergraduate at UIC, take our test prep courses to improve your scores in standardized tests such as TOEFL, IELTS and the GRE.  Use your improved test scores to enroll in a university graduate program.         Welcome from the director    At the Tutorium, our highly qualified and experienced staff and instructors will help you achieve your academic, professional, social, and personal goals. Students at the Tutorium are part of the larger community of University of Illinois at Chicago, a public research university and among the top five most diverse campuses in the nation.    Jason Romano | Director, Tutorium in Intensive English            Learn how we can help you become a UIC student  We can help you achieve your academic dreams and goals.   Click to learn more about our paths to academic success            About Us    Back to main content           Mission, Vision & Values    Our Team    Tutorium Paths to University Study    Contact Us     Agents                    UIC Logo        The Tutorium         Main Menu    Intensive English    Other Programs    Student Life    About Us 